entities.description: [Inbound / Outbound] | SBC Steering Port Limit - REQ0086932
entities.interimSummary:
Summary:
IC 2015 R2 P12

Problem:
SBC Core Steering Port limit inhibiting transfers and/or new calls

Timeline:
Jan 11: Tested M6 in CaaS General and found a memory leak resulting in high mem utilization (as discussed last week also).
Unable to upgrade at this time, we do see that our current code in PCI, 720M5P4 seems to be very stable exception of steering pool issue, not to mention we were able to handle peak without any major issues on M5P4.

Jan 25: Update from Oracle
The issue is with Development at this time.
The defect relating to the memory issue reported by another customer on 720M6, is not yet resolved. 
Development has also indicated that they will not create a workspace with the steering-pool port fix based off of the 720m5p4 image. 

Feb 4: Update from Oracle
Oracle has provided us a workspace (aka hot-fix) and we're installing it to CaaS General tonight for testing. If there are no issues after running on this patch for a week, we will work with the Kohl's team to schedule installation to CaaS PCI.

Feb 10: Testing the fix tonight for Mem leak issue (alongside steering port fix).

March 10: Steering Pool + Mem Leak fix unsuccessful in PCI (noted SBC crash, non-impacting)

April 8: DEN PCI SBC Upgrade with new patch from Oracle for Steering Pool fix.

April 11: We found that after applying M6 patch on PCI DEN SBC, there were audio issues (lack of audio) at the station side. We performed an emergency rollback to M5 on these boxes to prevent any customer impact. We are continuing to work with Oracle on a workspace image.

April 22: We have received a workspace from Oracle on steering pool issue. We were able to verify this new Workspace is bootable in our lab. Awaiting confirmation from Network as to the next DEN SBC upgrade.

entities.description: Issue in getting calls thru DC3 IVR to MSS_eCommerce
entities.interimSummary:
Problem:
Caller called in stating that he is having issues in receiving calls in the E-commerce sales queue. 
He states that he is not receiving any calls from that queue. 
In all other queues the no. of calls are getting changed but only the e-commerce sales queue is completely frozen. 
Business impact: DC 3 service team in not receiving any calls ecommerce sales queue

Analysis:
As noted by Mark Battaglia, agents *are* in fact receiving calls - just that calls may be going to queue earlier than expected based upon a wave configuration.

*Actual Issue*:
Dial 8555645705
Option 2 - DC3
Option 2 - New Orders (does nothing / cannot get to speak to agent)

Resolution:
This was due to the HOO "Holiday" IPtable having an entry for EC (and further, RWD, MSSRD) Group that specified a "FlashSale" holiday on 20160430 from 7am to 23:44.
When this was set to Active: False, this resolved the issue.

Followup:
Mark B. is following up internally to identify when/how this was put into place. It is expected that someone tried to use this for a pre/post or promotional wave entry improperly.
Jake to followup with database / report analysis for further audit information as well.
